examples.en: Pollution poses a threat to fish.
Her disappearance poses a real mystery.
The shortage of teachers poses a major problem.
This stand poses a threat to peace.
Drug abuse poses a major threat to the fabric of our society.
We believe it poses a serious danger to our national security.
The wildfire poses no immediate threat to any houses in the area.
Critics say the factory poses a potential threat to the environment.
In her book she poses the question,'How much do we need to be happy?'
The surgery has become a very routine operation and poses little danger.
The continuing increase in population numbers poses some awkward questions for the government.
Officials claim the chemical poses no real threat.
The chemical pollution poses a threat to the population at large.
They accused the company of trying to obscure the fact that the product poses a health risk.
